cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the performance evaluation of heterogeneous networks with inter-cell interference coordination techniques in LTE Advanced.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper involves optimization of system parameters to improve the capacity and fairness of the network.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the coordination and control of interference in a cellular network.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of interference coordination techniques on the throughput of picocell-edge users.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with security or cryptography, but it may be relevant in the context of secure communication in cellular networks.
